sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Per sample, 50 mg of frozen brain tissue was lysed and nuclei extracted. Nuclei were then either enriched by DAPI-positive FANS for single cell gene expression library generation or cleaned with a sucrose gradient centrifugation for single cell ATAC library generation., 10X Genomics 3' Single Cell Gene Expression v2/v3 , 10X Genomics Single Cell ATAC, snRNA-seq, snATAC-seq
sample_description: nuclear RNA, same donor as RL2366
sample_data_processing: cellranger mkfastq with Cellranger v3.1 to generate fastq files as inout for count pipeline., cellranger count with Cellranger v3.1 to generate feature-barcode matrices of gene expression., cellranger-atac mkfastq with Cellranger-ATAC v1.2 to generate fastq files as input for count pipeline., cellranger-atac count with Cellranger-ATAC v1.2 to generate BED-like tabular file with contains frgaments captured by the assay and barcode information in single cell output tables.
supplementary_files_format_and_content: For snRNA-seq data: feature-barcode matrices in HDF5 format containing every barcode from the fixed list of known-good barcode sequences that has at least 1 read for raw_feature files, or only containing detected cellular barcodes for filtered_feature files. For snATAC, a BED-like tabular fragment file with each line representing a unique ATAC-seq fragment captured by the assay,  an index for the fragments file as well as a singlecell file containing cell barcodes, QC information and ATAC signal ...

For snATAC, a BED-like tabular fragment file with each line representing a unique ATAC-seq fragment captured by the assay,  an index for the fragments file as well as a singlecell file containing cell barcodes, QC information and ATAC signal ...
